** combination reaction : it is type of reaction in which two or more chemical combine together to form single result is known as combination reaction:
eg: hydrogen+ oxygen= water:

** decomposistion:
  here big chemical breaks down smaller one :
AB= A+B:
  quick lime used in making cement:
CACO3= CAO+CO2
  here quick lime is CaO:

** for decomposing any of the chemical reaction we need energy that energy can be:
i)heat energy:   thermal decompostion
ii)electric energy: electrolytic decomposition:
iii)light(photochemical energy): photodecompostion:

** thermal decomposition: here when we heat the chemical reaction it gets broken into diff diff form 
eg: FESO4= FE2SO3+SO2+SO3
  FESO4= FERROSU SULPHATE:
  FE2SO3=FERRIC OXIDE:

  HERE ferrous sulphate are green in colour and when you heat they will break in ferric oxide and leter so2 and so3 are gas pollutants gas:
** so its thermal decompostion and Endothermic reaction:


** electrolysys:
here the process of decompostion using electric current thats why it is called electrolysis:
h20= h2+o so here h2 goes to cathode and o2 gose to anode

**oxidation: if any chemical reaction gains oxygen then it is called oxidation and loose hydrogen :
** reduction: if any chemical reaction loose oxygen and gains hydrogen it is reduction:
** redox reaction: reaction in which oxidation and reduction happen is said to be redox:

** corosion: when metal is atcaked by its sorrounding element such as moisture and water vapour then it is said to be corrode and process is said as corroison:
** rusting of iron: iron+ oxygen+ h20= corroison

  ** ranidity: when the taste of eating food material gets changed then it is said as rancidity:
